                   TwitterUserDiGraph G,
                   boolean[] retweeted,
                   int curTime,

                   java.util.Vector<java.lang.Integer> printArray)
        This function performs a breadth first search on the twitter user digraph
        Parameters:
        source - - An integer representing the starting vertex (source of the fake news) in the graph
        size - - An integer representing the number of vertices (twitter users) in the graph
        G - - A digraph representing the twitter population
        retweeted - - A boolean array denoting if a given user has retweeted a fake news tweet yet
        curTime - - An integer representing the current time (Remember that we monitor a tweet for a day to see the impact it has)
        printArray - - A vector of Integers representing the twitter users that retweeted the tweet on that specific iteration
        timeElapsed - - An integer representing the amount of time passed from when the tweet originated from
